>Why is North American folklore/mythology so damn rare?
Well, the indigenous folklore was mostly oral tradition, and the Europeans did a damn good job stamping that out. What remains of it is pretty sparse and not well-traveled. Then there's the...what we'll call for lack of a better term, American Gods problem. The melting pot of American culture also included the various myths and legends of immigrants, which supplanted the local flavor. I'd say if you want the true North American as we know it today, you have to look towards the frontier legends. The Tall Tales, folk heroes, and cryptids, and the Urban Legends that followed. Little Grey Aliens and Men In Black Suits are our mythology.
